Let me clarify: I don’t do specific brand recommendations for clothing on Twitter or in my articles. But you can always hire me to shop for you or give you advice on where and how to shop better. That’s like my whole thing 😭
But also, the idea that sustainable brands are universally ugly is just false. Hanifa is a sustainable brand, for example.

I don’t do general brand recommendations for clothes because most sustainable brands are very loyal to their aesthetic, and I couldn’t possibly cover every aesthetic for everyone. It’s not like fast fashion that sells something for everyone to maximize profits. They’re niche.

Hence why I always stress having a solid list of the things you actually want and need and seeking those out to find brands that offer the things you know you like and that work for you so you know where to look.

Good sustainable brands aren’t going to be fed to us the same way fast fashion brands are because most of them don’t have the marketing budget or the ubiquitousness. You have to start actively searching for and following brands that speak to you to change your algorithm.
